    {
      "id": "de6d12388e570a59e289cf74f1f79af55e768478",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-19 21:09:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\n(22 comments)\n\nI haven't closely reviewed all of the details of the implementation (hopefully Alex will understand all of it).  My main concern is about the protocol/compatibility change.  At a minimum, this should change a magic value somewhere so that existing systems (e.g. James') would not try to recover from older logs.\n\nIf this is only changing the recovery llog files on disk (which are consumed internally to the MDS that wrote them) and not the network protocol, then it should be enough to just change the magic and ensure that recovery code checks the magic and either skips old ones or requires the recovery complete on the old version before starting the new one.\n\nIf this is changing the OUT network protocol that is also in use by LFSCK to OSTs then we need to work harder to ensure interoperability.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "c55eb94a9ec4c0d7f6b76e73895378af91f6454a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-06-19 23:22:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nAndreas: the update llog will not exit until 2.8. All of changes here is about the update log (disk or network), so there should not be compatibility issue. IMHO.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
